{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## S7 implemented + verified LIVE — 2026-06-30 (commits db5d7401 + header fix)\n\n**Phase A — live gate validation:**\n- FULL-CHAIN E2E (transient, on a deletable test branch per the apply-prove-rollback scope, so real `main` is not advanced): pushed change #81 to refs/for/gerrit-e2e-test -> the review-bot reviewed via review_code and cast LLM-Review=+1 -> submitted in Gerrit (status MERGED) -> the replication plugin pushed gerrit-e2e-test to GitHub -> `git ls-remote github gerrit-e2e-test` showed the merged commit (commit msg \"S7 e2e: full chain review->submit->replicate\"). Then cleaned up (branch deleted both sides, refspec reverted). The direct-push / PR-merge REJECTION half was proven in S6.\n- MONITORING: `infra/terraform/monitoring.tf` applied -> SNS topic `rebar-gerrit-alerts` (+ email sub to SSM `/rebar/prod/alert-endpoint`, pending its one-time confirmation) + 3 alarms wired to SNS: `rebar-gerrit-gate-down` (Rebar/Gate:GerritReachable < 1, treat_missing_data=breaching), `rebar-gerrit-ec2-system-check`, `rebar-gerrit-ec2-instance-check` (host-down backstop). observability.sh now publishes Rebar/Gate:GerritReachable.\n- ALARM DELIVERY PROVEN: forced gate-down (set-alarm-state ALARM) -> SNS published -> a temporary SQS subscriber RECEIVED the notification (\"ALARM: rebar-gerrit-gate-down\"). Cleaned up; alarm reset to OK.\n\n**Phase B — recoverability + runbooks:**\n- NON-DESTRUCTIVE RESTORE DRILL: on-demand snapshot of vol-06fa2e77a9dd97527 -> throwaway gp3 volume from it -> attached at /dev/sdg -> mounted READ-ONLY at /mnt/restore-drill -> VERIFIED the Gerrit NoteDb repos present (All-Projects.git, All-Users.git, rebar.git) -> detached + deleted the throwaway volume + the drill snapshot. The live prevent_destroy data volume was never touched (confirmed in-use/attached after).\n- DLM: S1 owns the daily snapshot policy (retain=7); monitoring.tf only ASSERTS the backup target via a `check` block (no second DLM resource).\n- RUNBOOKS (infra/runbooks/): provision-restore.md (RTO/freeze-and-restore, snapshot id, the non-destructive drill, prevent_destroy removal, plan-before-apply), gerrit-upgrade.md, review-bot-ops.md — which clearly documents the **`/rerun`** manual re-review (WHERE /review/rerun, HOW the authenticated curl with the SSM token + change id, WHEN to recover a stuck fail-closed -1 vs the vote-less-only reconciler, fail-closed; xref ADR-0009).\n\n**Code review (subagent):** VERDICT PASS — dimensionless metric/alarm contract holds, all 3 alarms can fire, no duplicate/destructive terraform, restore drill genuinely non-destructive, /rerun docs thorough. NIT folded (observability.sh header refreshed to list all metric sections). No secrets in any committed monitoring/runbook file."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782817091755136001,"uuid":"c32bb231-cf73-42f9-a7db-a707529aebc7"}